The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	Laxmi Ratan Shukla was retained as the Bengal skipper on Monday, for the forth coming Ranji Trophy season where they will be participating in the Plate Division. The CAB officials are slated to meet on October 27 to select the Bengal squad for the first two Ranji ties.           
	 The Premier Skills Advanced Course organised by the British Council kicked off at the SAI, Eastern Centre on Monday. British coaches will train 40 local coaches who have been selected from the northern and eastern zones.           
	 Debutant Md. Sayeed Seventh blanked seventh seed Aamer Hossain 3-0 in the BRC State Snooker Championship being played at the Bengal Rowing Club on Monday. Manish Jain had it easy against Sagar Malhotra, beating him 3-0, while former Bengal champion Neeraj Khemka beat Mahfooz Alam 3-0.                
